                     <interp inst="def1-3038-18431023" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-3038-18431023" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN JOHNSON</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-3038-18431023" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-3038-18431023" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-3038-18431023" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-3038-18431023" type="surname" value="HALEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-3038-18431023" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES HALEY</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18431023-3038-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18431023-3038-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18431023-3038-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> steal<lb></lb>ing, on the <rs id="t18431023-cd-182" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18431023-3038-offence-1 t18431023-cd-182"></join>13th of Oct</rs>., 49lbs. weight of nails, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18431023-name-1235" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1235" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1235" type="surname" value="REID"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1235" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18431023-3038-offence-1 t18431023-name-1235"></join>Wil<lb></lb>liam Reid</persName> and others: and that Haley had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184310230174"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1236" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1236" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1236" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1236" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a veterinary surgeon, employed on the premises of William Reid and others, in Liquorpond-street—they had some nails of a particular sort—I lost some of them, to the value of about 40<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I beleive these produced are them—they correspond in every respect.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What nails are they? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> For horses shoes—I gave the description for the pattern of them—I have never seen any like them—I cannot say when I had last seen any of these—we have missed nails for the last two years; but I cannot say that all these left at one time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1237" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1237" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1237" type="surname" value="DURANT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1237" type="given" value="LEWIS"></interp>LEWIS DURANT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Mr. Branscomb, an ironmonger—we supply the prosecutors with these nails—they are made for no one but them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Have you not reason to believe that there are other nails of this sort made? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I do not think there are—they are drawn from under the head very differently to what the generality of nails are.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1238" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1238" type="surname" value="REDMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1238" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY REDMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 140.) I stopped the prisoners with these nails in Goswell-street, on the evening of the 13th of October—Haley had them on his head—I asked Johnson if they belonged to him—he said they did, and that he bdught horse-parings—Haley said he worked for Johnson.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did he not say he bought horse-parings all over London? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and that he picked the nails out of the horse-parings—I believe these nails have not been on a horse's foot.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1239" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1239" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1239" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1239" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I believe people in shoeing horses, drop some nails on the ground—a poor man going about buying the horse-parings might get a few nails, but very few, and they would not be in this condition—a few of these are rusty, but not many.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Haley's Defence.</hi> I am in the employ of Johnson; we travel all over London; I have the sifting of the parings, and I put the new nails on one side, the old ones on the other, and take them to a farrier's shop and sell them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1240" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1240" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1240" type="surname" value="GINGER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1240" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH GINGER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 137.) I produce a certificate of Haley's former conviction, which I got from Mr. Clark's office—(<hi rend="italic">read</hi>)—the prisoner is the person.</p>
               <p>
